7
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:08,840
(Episode 8: Fling and Fight)

8
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:25,360
I... I think we should

9
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:29,680
check out the filming location

10
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,600
next time.

11
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,080
Okay.

12
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,039
(Standard FM, Metropolitan Area)

13
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,880
-Thank you.
-Hey.

14
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,520
Don't you have anything to say to me?

15
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,680
-No, I don't.
-What? "No"?

16
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,360
Hey, wait. But...

17
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:56,920
She's unbelievable.

18
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,160
What's her deal?

19
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,960
Dong-chan and that woman
went there by themselves?

20
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,680
It's the assistant director's job to help
the director find a location.

21
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,840
Ha-young,
do you still have feelings for Dong-chan?

22
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,440
I don't think I need
to answer that question.

23
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,960
Isn't he a little out of your league?

24
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,920
Even if it's the trend to date
younger men, let's be realistic.

25
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,640
Watch what you say.

26
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,560
He sets his own standards.

27
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,840
He doesn't care what other people think.

28
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,600
That's why I fell in love with him.

29
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,079
But that's not the problem.

30
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:31,440
Yes, of course.
That's not the actual problem.

31
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,440
Hello?

32
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,480
Today, don't worry about anything else

33
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,240
and just get some rest.

34
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,480
I'm sorry.

35
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,160
(I really have no excuses,)

36
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,360
but I thought I should at least apologize.

37
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,880
What exactly are you apologizing for?

38
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,839
For kissing you.

39
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:25,840
-I'm sorry.
-You're sorry?

40
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,280
I thought I was going to die.

41
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:30,560
I wanted to kiss someone before I died.

42
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:36,360
But I didn't die.
I ended up staying alive.

43
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,440
Right. Well...

44
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,120
I'm relieved that you didn't die.

45
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,600
You should get some rest.
We can talk about it later.

46
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,080
What do you mean?

47
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,400
Let's just wrap it up here.

48
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:56,400
Will you accept my apology?

49
00:04:56,560 --> 00:05:00,360
Is that something
you have to apologize for?

50
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,800
That's what I think.

51
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,120
You refused.

52
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,640
You're so petty.

53
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,640
I thought I was dying.

54
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,400
Hold on.

55
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,760
What is going on?

56
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,800
Fine, then. I'll wait for my punishment.

57
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,320
Do as you wish.

58
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,840
Hello? What? Hello?

59
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,680
What was that?

60
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,040
What does she want?

61
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,920
What should I do?

62
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,840
I should've just died then and there.

63
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,920
I'm so irritated.

64
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,920
I'm so embarrassed!

65
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,159
What is this?

66
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,520
-Hello?
(-It's me.)

67
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,600
Hey, did you meet that NIS executive?

68
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,360
That's why I called you.

69
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,800
Are you busy?

70
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:57,080
I think Nikolai died last year.

71
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,040
Since he was
the strongest presidential candidate,

72
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:02,560
people are trying to cover this up
due to political reasons.

73
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,080
But they believe he was assassinated

74
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,520
by the opposing party.

75
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,320
The CIA said so.

76
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:12,800
Then is Nikolai the one
who blew up Professor Hwang's car?

77
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,000
I don't think so.

78
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:17,000
Apparently,
there's a book about the individuals

79
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:19,960
he had killed during his mafia days.

80
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:23,120
It's like an epic that the mafias have.

81
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,160
It wasn't published,

82
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,720
but it says, during the attack
of Professor Johnson McCarthy,

83
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:29,600
he claimed to have killed

84
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,200
Professor Hwang who was his assistant.

85
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:32,600
So you're saying

86
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:36,240
in 1984,
he believed Professor Hwang was dead?

87
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,440
That's right.

88
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,800
I knew it.

89
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,760
Nikolai wasn't the culprit.

90
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,440
Do you have a hunch?

91
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,720
I'm not sure.

92
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:49,360
I'll know for sure once
Professor Hwang regains his memory.

93
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,680
Anyway, I'll be going.

94
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,680
(October 24, 1998)

95
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,240
(Hwamin Bank)

96
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:36,159
Should I look for
a studio apartment or a rooftop?

97
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:39,840
I need to live near my love.

98
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:42,640
She must see me often.
She must get used to me.

99
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,480
I'll plan out my own fate.

100
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,000
(Monthly rent 220,000 won)

101
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:56,320
(Monthly rent 220,000 won)

102
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,960
Lady Luck is on my side.

103
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,200
How could the rooftop house
at Mi-ran's place be vacant?

104
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:08,320
The deities are doing their best
to help my love life.

105
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,080
I can't believe this.

106
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,720
This is fate.

107
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,400
Hello?

108
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:25,000
I called to say that I'm interested in
moving into the rooftop house.

109
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,960
Gosh, that was quick.

110
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,360
Hello?

111
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,320
But you see, we'd prefer our tenant

112
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:36,799
to be a college student.

113
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,080
And if possible, female.

114
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,799
How old are you?

115
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,480
I'm 44 years old.

116
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:47,080
I'm sorry,

117
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:49,560
-but we're only interested--
(-I'm not a student,)

118
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,280
but I am a professor.

119
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:54,160
Oh, are you?

120
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:56,560
Yes. I need to experience

121
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,520
the life in a rooftop house.

122
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:01,080
I'm studying the correlation
between isolation

123
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:04,680
(and psychological emancipation.)

124
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:07,320
I'd like to visit.

125
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,320
Do you have time?

126
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,400
(Kim Hong-suk)

127
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,960
-Hello?
(-Hey, it's me.)

128
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,680
(Where are you? Are you doing field work?)

129
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:23,960
(Would you like to have dinner with me?)

130
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,680
All right.

131
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:33,760
-Did he agree to come?
-Of course, sir.

132
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,240
He always listens to me.

133
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:40,800
You see, I helped him a lot in the past.

134
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,600
Don't be ridiculous.

135
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,320
You don't have to bluff in front of me.

136
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,600
I know he's not the type
to leech off of others.

137
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:49,680
Right.

138
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:55,440
-Do you need to get on his good side?
-Yes, sir.

139
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,280
Okay. Let's go.

140
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,680
Yes, sir.

141
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:03,840
This is an important day for us

142
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,400
to meet with our savior.

143
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:07,320
"Savior"?

144
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,560
Being smart won't get you far in politics.

145
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:11,560
Neither does being passionate.

146
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,760
It's all about the money.

147
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:17,560
I see.

148
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,400
Why is he acting so friendly?

149
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:24,160
By the way, what is she up to?

150
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,600
Is she doing all right?

151
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:28,680
I'm worried when she's quiet
and when she calls.

152
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,120
She's the essence of my worries.

153
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,280
(I wanted to kiss someone before I died.)

154
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:37,920
Could it have been her first kiss?

155
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,720
There's no way.

156
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,320
No way. No.

157
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,760
We're having soy bean stew for dinner.

158
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,720
Nam-tae called and said he was craving it.

159
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,560
I'm getting really heated,
so I'm going to get some air.

160
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,880
Let's go out together after having dinner.

161
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,560
No, I'll go alone.

162
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:24,520
I don't deserve to eat.

163
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,680
What's wrong? Did something happen?

164
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:32,240
You're going to break your teeth.
Be gentle.

165
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:36,000
We have a candidate for our rooftop house.

166
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:38,040
Do you want to interview them together?

167
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,680
No, thanks.
I'm not good at reading people.

168
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,120
I'm garbage.

169
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,200
Hey.

170
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:17,640
Hi. You know me, right? I'm Kim Si-seok.

171
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:19,280
Hello, sir. It's been a long time.

172
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,560
Sit down.

173
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:28,920
I remember how you caused
a commotion when you first joined.

174
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,320
They said a variety show director

175
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,440
was more handsome than the actors.

176
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:35,360
The female reporters
and employees at the station

177
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,080
were head over heels for you.

178
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,840
That's right.

179
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:43,440
People thought he got in solely
because of his good looks

180
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:45,520
back when I was the chief,

181
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:48,880
and he was the president of the station.

182
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:56,320
Choose a menu.

183
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,440
Yes, sir.

184
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,160
(Set Menu, Lunch Special)

185
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,800
This place is expensive.

186
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,000
I'd like "Today's Menu", please.

187
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,400
A salaryman like me

188
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:11,560
can't dare to have something this
expensive for dinner.

189
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:13,480
Don't worry about me

190
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:15,440
and have what you want.

191
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:17,000
Look here.

192
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,920
I heard there's this new law

193
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:21,800
about the entertaining fee's limit
being 30,000 won or less.

194
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,480
This world has become a better place,
hasn't it?

195
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:26,840
Look, Dong-chan.

196
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:31,600
I'll pay for my own food.

197
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:35,600
By the way,
do you have plans to get into politics?

198
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,240
I'm not a resident of your area.

199
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,400
You shouldn't invest your time in me.

200
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
He must be here.

201
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:57,560
-Hello.
-I'm sorry for being late.

202
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:00,000
-I'm Kim Hong-suk.
-It's nice to meet you.

203
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,720
Please sit down.

204
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,880
Okay.

205
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:24,680
He's Chairman Lee Seok-du of Unsung Group.

206
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:34,720
Hello, I'm Ma Dong-chan.

207
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:36,960
Yes, I'm aware.

208
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,360
(Real Estate Lease Contract)

209
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:47,640
(Landlord: Ko Yu-han,
Tenant: Hwang Dong-Hyuk)

210
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,840
My daughter is attending
this university too.

211
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:54,920
I know...

212
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,680
I mean, really?

213
00:14:57,880 --> 00:15:00,680
Actually,
I have a son who is over 30 years old

214
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:03,760
but has the mentality of
a child younger than 10 years old.

215
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,960
That's why I decided to rent out
the rooftop house.

216
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:10,160
Bravo! Good job. I'm so glad you did.

217
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:16,400
You seem like a really cheerful guy.

218
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:19,120
Yes. You'll get to know me more in time,

219
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,080
but I'm a great guy.

220
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:27,440
Sure. We'll see.

221
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,600
You can talk casually to me.

222
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,320
Father.

223
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:35,640
Please let me call you that.
I would like to do that.

224
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,560
Mi-ran.

225
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,720
(They resemble each other so much.)

226
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:55,720
(The height, the build,
and the frame of the face too.)

227
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:03,200
(Korean Style Restaurant Jinsagalbi)

228
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:09,560
I should've cooled down
my room in advance.

229
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,800
(Car to home)

230
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:12,920
(Updating your home's device)

231
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:13,840
(Air conditioning: off)

232
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:18,040
(On)

233
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,000
(Air conditioning: on)

234
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,160
There.

235
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:29,000
A new sun will rise tomorrow.

236
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,520
Just be cool and ignore it.
That's more like me.

237
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,400
(Cold-hearted Punk)

238
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,840
(Missed Call)

239
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:53,400
Right. We're awkward right now.

240
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,680
I forgot all about it.

241
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,320
Then...

242
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:00,720
I'll text her instead.

243
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:04,400
(You shouldn't take the fever-reducing
shot more than once a day.)

244
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,640
(Since you got a shot today,
you must not take another.)

245
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:08,560
(Cold-hearted Punk)

246
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:11,440
(I should've told you earlier.
I'm sorry I told you so late.)
(Cold-hearted Punk)

247
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:12,319
(Cold-hearted Punk)

248
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:15,040
I was a little out of it today too.

249
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:20,240
What does he mean by that?
Why was he out of it?

250
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,640
Why? Why?

251
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:26,440
Was he that offended by my kiss?

252
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:28,560
I was a little out of it today.

253
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:31,600
Or maybe

254
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:34,200
he liked it.

255
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:35,920
I was a little out of it

256
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,240
today.

257
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,280
Did it make him ecstatic?

258
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,840
What does he mean?

259
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,600
Why? Why?

260
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:49,480
Why?

261
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:53,800
What a crazy day. I should go to sleep.

262
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:43,880
-Good morning.
-Hi.

263
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,080
Dong-chan.

264
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,560
Thank you.

265
00:18:57,320 --> 00:18:59,880
By the way, can I talk casually to you?

266
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,000
You already are.

267
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:06,280
I'll call you
Dong-chan if you'll allow me.

268
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:08,800
Weren't you already calling me by my name?

269
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:13,440
All right. Let's get to work.

